<p>I am an Associate Professor in <a href="https://www.cs.purdue.edu/">Dept. of Computer Science</a> at <a href="https://www.purdue.edu/">Purdue University</a>. Previously, I was an Assistant Professor in the <a href="https://cse.osu.edu/">Dept. of Computer Science and Engineering</a> at <a href="https://www.osu.edu/">the Ohio State University</a> after I received my Ph.D. in <a href="https://www.cs.ucla.edu/">Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.ucla.edu/">University of California, Los Angeles</a>. Prior to UCLA, I worked as an Associate/Assistant Researcher at Wireless Networking Group at <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/lab/microsoft-research-asia/">Microsoft Research Asia</a>. I received a M.Eng and B.Eng in Automation from Tsinghua University, both with highest honors. In the past, I held internships at IBM TJ Watson Research Center, Microsoft Research Redmond and Microsoft Research Asia. I am an ACM Distinguished Member. </p>
<p>My current research interests are in the broad areas of <b>mobile networking, security and systems</b>, with a recent focus on renovating radio access technologies (RATs) in 5G and 6G, AI for networks, 5G/IoT security, and Physical AI (mainly for autonomous drones and robots with spatial intelligence).</p>
<p><a href="cv-chunyi-short.pdf">Curriculum Vitae</a>
</p>
