<h2>Tutorial on AIM, MobileInsight and beyond</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>This is a brief summary of high-level position talk to the public. It has basic idea, approaches and main results, by skipping all technical details of each research problem under this umbrella project: (<a href="./talks/AIM-summary-public.pps">pps</a>), (<a href="./talks/AIM-summary-public.pdf">PDF</a>).
</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><p>This is <a href="./talks/mobileinsight-hackaton-201808-full-final.pptx">a tutorial</a> of L2/L1 latency analysis enabled by MobileInsight. It was originally used for <a href="https://conferences.sigcomm.org/sigcomm/2018/hackathon.html">Hackathon, co-located at ACM SIGCOMM</a> on Aug 25, 2018, and then was  reorganized and substantially enhanced for public distribution (step-by-step learning and practice). The used codes and sample logs can be found 
<a href="./hackathon18-workspace">here</a>. You can find the codes developed by the hackathon team (Quentin, Maryam, Syed and Ensar) at <a href="https://github.com/qdeconinck/hackathon-2018-mobileinsight">github</a>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><p>This is an 3-hr tutorial on <a href="http://globecom2017.ieee-globecom.org/content/tutorials">GlobeCom&rsquo;17</a> on Dec 8, 2017. 
It introduces how to step-by-step verify mobile network operations on your phones via MobileInsight. Here is the tutorial slide (<a href="./talks/globecom17-tutorial-mobileinsight-public.pdf"">pdf</a>) (<a href="./talks/globecom17-tutorial-mobileinsight-public.ppsx">ppsx</a>). For more up-to-date information, please check our <a href="http://mobileinsight.net">MobileInsight</a> website.</p>
</li>
</ul>
